<br>
I'll break it down for you again.  I'll even go a bit further in the break down.  A slight change I will have to make is the double bs percentage.  I could get no accurate info on the change in double bs percentages even from high lvl rogues.  What I got were guesses and estimates so I did a test at 58 I attempt a double 55% of the time.  at 55 it was 40%. I'm going to take a wild guess and say its a linear progression making the double bs percentage at 60 65%.<br>
<br>
I'm skipping the rounds in which you mess up your bs attempt for the round due to bad execution of lag.<br>
<br>
First the regular combat. 0-4 attacks.  Max hit with a 15 dmg weapon will be roughly 96.  Average should be around 1/2 max.  To this a 4x weapon dmg bonus will be added.  I'll just assume both weapons are 15 dmg.  Average duelist hit will be 108.  Given a double attack, duel wield and hit ratio of 2/3 you will get an average of around 2 landed melee hits per round (if you want to be exact its 1.81 but you can't really get 1.81 hits now can you). To break this down.<br>
<br>
Main hand- 1 x 1.66 (double attacks) x .66(misses)<br>
Offhand   - 1x .66(duel wield) x 1.66(double attacks)<br>
<br>
So average dmg per duelist round via normal melee will be roughly 216<br>
<br>
Next we have to look at backstab. As stated hit ratio should be around 2/3 double bs same. Max dmg without an uber +bs skill weapon during duelist is 1106 I'll assume the average is somewhere 1/2 max or 553 as with all melee.<br>
<br>
Types of rounds.<br>
<br>
Single or double miss(18%)<br>
Average bs dmg 0<br>
Average regular melee dmg 216<br>
Average total dmg per round 216<br>
<br>
Single hit or double with 1 hit(52%)<br>
Average bs dmg 553<br>
Average regular melee dmg 216<br>
Average total dmg per round 769<br>
<br>
Double hit (30%)<br>
Average bs dmg 1106<br>
Average regular melee dmg 216<br>
Average total dmg per round 1322<br>
<br>
Almost 20% of the time its a wash and the caster laughs it off (if he isn't snared heh)<br>
<br>
About 50% of the time it hurts.<br>
<br>
About 30% of the time you stand a good chance of dying from it if you don't have your skin up or yonder immediately.<br>
<br>
You could average it out to about a bit over 800 dmg (it is a bit higher than I thought earlier because of the double bs percentage thing I mentioned) per round but the above breakdown gives you better info I think.<br>
<br>
Basicly what were going towards is that indoors a rogue running around golem wanding and duelist smacking wizards indoors will probably kill 3/10 right off. (1 for every 1.5k he burns) Gee wonder why wands aren't used more?  There is VERY good chance that the wizard at that point will either be healed by his group, gate, or run.<br>
<br>
Outdoors I suggest you yonder upon being insta dispelled.  The rogue will get tired of burning gobs of plat.  Then it will be reserved for a finishing blow when your hp drops down low enough for a single average round to drop you.  Nothing like a one hit one kill MB.  <br>
<br>
Even with hp that low it should if you play it right have a reasonably high flub factor. (in other words try to avoid exposing your back, back off when he starts to circle you to bs, start and stop quickly to make him waste duelist on a failed attempt)  <br>
<br>
